job_description:
Do you have a previous experience in data management and are you a great communicator? Are you familiar with the concepts such as Master Data Management, Data Migrations, Data Governance? If so, we’d love to hear from you.
You would be joining our Global KYC Delivery Tribe working on the development of state-of-the-art data solutions for socially relevant topics such as Anti-Money Laundering, Counter Terrorism Financing, Fraud, Sanctions and their global implementation across 20+ countries, affecting 36 million ING customers. You will help deliver our customers an optimal KYC experience whilst remaining compliant and in control of the gatekeeper function of the Bank.
Our Global Know Your Customer organization is a department inside ING Global providing all ING entities with standardized solutions in various KYC related processes.
The opportunity – Data Management Specialist in the Data Strategy Squad
As a Data Management Specialist will ensure that the data of our ING customers is efficiently handled as part of our Data Strategy Squad. Through your knowledge of end-to-end data flows within a complex IT architectural landscape, you will define requirements, processes and controls that guarantee complete and correct data out of 20+ countries is available to different KYC applications which process millions of relevant events daily.
Having a passion for data and championing the principles behind data management is key to being successful in this role. Through your contribution, you will be enhancing the data management framework of the GKYC tribe, while driving & influencing the global data policies across ING and its subsidiaries.
What you'll do:
You will help ING prevent Money Laundering and Financial Crimes globally;
Solving complex IT/Data problems and challenges;
Through your Data Management knowledge and experience you will help to define/improve/enhance the way in which data is gathered, controlled and processed by the KYC department;
You will define Data Democratization processes so that the Data can be used efficiently and consistently;
You are responsible for analyzing the data requirements, developing the governance framework and controls across the E2E chain for the use of data in products and services in the KYC scope;
You are always looking to optimize and automate processes and data, knowing how to include quality by design;
You simplify solutions and processes in a complex and fragmented IT landscape and tell the story clearly to various international stakeholders;
You stimulate cross-border interaction and alignment between people, Tribes, Squads, Chapters, FO organizations, Local KYC activities and Service organizations;
You refine stories in a straightforward and executional way to optimize velocity;
You give and ask for constructive feedback;
You build the bridge between business and IT.
How to succeed
You have a bachelor or master’s degree (IT, Engineering, Maths or Economics/Business is a plus);
You have a minimum of +1 years of working experience defining Data Management processes and/or tooling implementation (Consulting experience is a big plus) using tools such as IBM IGC or similar, (being comfortable with SQL is a plus);
You have +2 years of experience working on IT related projects having SDLC at its core;
You have a certain degree of understanding of data architecture and data modelling and where this impacts the business process.
You have defined and/or implemented solutions using concepts such as Data Migrations, Data Management, Data Presentation/Visualization in a context with large volume of Data;
You have experience in contributing to regulatory/processes changes and translating regulatory requirements into functional designs and/or processes (experience within the areas of Financial Economic Crime, Anti Money Laundering or Compliance is a plus);
You are an energetic & approachable professional;
You can easily “switch context” – so you are able to drive multiple (and distinct) topics during the day within an Agile environment where change is constant;
You are a strong analytical and abstract thinker;
You have excellent communication, presentation, networking and influencing skills;
You are fluent in English (speaking and writing).
Rewards & benefits
We want to make sure that it’s possible for you to strike the right balance between your career and your private life.
The benefits of working with us at ING include:
A salary tailored to your qualities and experience
24-27 vacation days depending on contract
Pension scheme
13th month salary
Individual Savings Contribution (BIS), 3.5% of your gross annual salary
8% Holiday payment
Personal growth and challenging work with endless possibilities
An informal working environment with innovative colleagues
Work Agile, so new ideas come to life faster
About us
With 57,000 employees and operations in approximately 40 countries, there is no shortage of opportunities for people with initiative who want to help people take a step ahead in life and in business. Do you want to work at the cutting edge of what’s possible and at the same time ensure you work with integrity and hold the customer’s interests at heart? Do you want to be surrounded by progressive, inspiring, diverse and supportive colleagues? Then there is no better place to invest your talents than at ING. Join us. Apply today.
